---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Hydrate - Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Hydrate - Simple Water Tracker iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/hydrate/privacy"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-12">Hydrate - Simple Water Tracker &middot; Effective February 15, 2026</p>

        <div class="space-y-8 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">The Short Version</h2>
            <p>Hydrate does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. Your water intake stays on your device.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
            <p>All hydration data, goals, streaks, and settings are stored locally on your device using SwiftData. No data is sent to any server, cloud service, or third party. There are no user accounts and no sign-up required.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Apple HealthKit</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">Hydrate can sync your water intake with Apple Health as dietary water data, but only if you explicitly grant permission. HealthKit data is governed by <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">Apple's privacy policy</a> and never leaves your device through Hydrate.</p>
            <p>If you deny HealthKit access, the app continues to work normally â€” your data is simply stored within Hydrate only. You can enable or disable HealthKit sync at any time in Settings.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Analytics & Tracking</h2>
            <p>Hydrate contains no analytics frameworks, no ad SDKs, no tracking pixels, and no telemetry of any kind. We do not use any third-party services that collect data.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Network Usage</h2>
            <p>Hydrate makes no network requests. The app works entirely offline. The only network activity associated with the app is through the App Store for updates.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Notifications</h2>
            <p>If you enable hydration reminders, notifications are scheduled locally on your device. No data is sent to any server to deliver notifications.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Hydrate does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Data Deletion</h2>
            <p>When you delete the Hydrate app, all your data is permanently deleted from your device. There is no cloud backup to remove because we never had your data in the first place.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>If this policy changes, we will update this page with the new effective date. Since Hydrate collects no data, meaningful changes are unlikely.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
